Some banners can only be originally created using non-renewable banner patterns, but the patterns aren't consumed when used, and the banners can then be duplicated by crafting them together with empty banners of same base color.
Use water cauldron to remove all layer of renewable Ominous Banner

Obtained by trading with cartographer villagers for Banner Pattern Globe‌[Java Edition only], Banner Pattern Flower, Banner Pattern Field Masoned, Banner Pattern Bordure Indented‌[Bedrock Edition only]
Formed when lava flows over soul soil next to blue ice.
Has a 5% chance to generate with a birch or oak tree from a sapling within 2 blocks of a flower.

Obtained by trading with armorer villagers, toolsmith villagers and weaponsmith villagers.

Coal is dropped by wither skeletons.
Charcoal is obtained by smelting logs or wood.
Charcoal also obtained from breaking campfires.

Cobblestone or stone blocks are created when water and flowing lava meet, which may then be mined.
Stone is obtained by smelting cobblestone.

Coral and Coral Fan grown by using bonemeal underwater in warm ocean biomes.
Coral Block obtained by trading with a wandering trader.
Obtained by bartering with a piglin.

Obtained by using a hoe on a rooted dirt created in place of a renewable moss block when a bone meal is use on an azelia, also yield one hanging roots in the process.
Obtained by using a hoe on a coarse dirt crafted using two dirt and two renewable gravel, which gives 4 coarse dirt for each crafting, resulting in a positive net gain.
Obtained by mining renewable podzol.

Obtained by trading with an armorer villager for armor, toolsmith villager for tool and weaponsmith villager for axe & sword.
Diamond armor can also be obtained as a rare drop from extremely rare zombies and skeletons, which spawn with them.
Obtained by using a glass bottle on the ender dragon's breath.

Obtained by trading with a mason villager.
Crafted from renewable pointed dripstone.

Ferns obtained by trading with a wandering trader.

All flowers (except wither rose) are obtained by trading with a wandering trader.
All short flowers (except wither rose) are obtained by using bone meal on grass blocks. Certain short flowers grow only in certain biomes.
Tall flowers are dropped when bone meal is used on them.
Wither roses are dropped by mobs killed by a wither.
Poppies are dropped by iron golems.
Poppies are gifted by baby villagers once the player gains Hero of the Village.‌[Java Edition only]
Gets dropped when a frog eats a magma cube.
Using bone meal on either type of nylium creates both types of fungi.

Obtained by trading with a librarian villager.

Obtained by fishing.

Dropped by witches.

Obtained by mining renewable glowstone.
Dropped if a goat rams into a tree‌[Bedrock Edition only].

Obtained by trading with a wandering trader.

Obtained by trading with a cleric villager.
Lapis Lazuli are gifted by cleric villagers once the player gains Hero of the Village.‌[Java Edition only]

Craftable from renewable string and slime
Dropped by wandering traders or trader llama when held with 2 lead.

The platform generated when a nether portal is generated in the air contains netherrack in addition to the obsidian that would be there normally. It is possible to break all the blocks of that portal, and go back through on the Nether side, and it generates another platform.‌[Bedrock Edition only]

Entering a nether portal for which there is no matching exit generates a new portal of 14 obsidian blocks (18 if it generates in mid air), which may be mined.
An entity travelling to the End regenerates the 5×5 obsidian platform, which may be mined.
The obsidian pillars in the End are regenerated when the ender dragon is respawned.
Created when a lava source block collides with water.
Obtained by bartering with piglins.
Obtained by breaking renewable Ender Chest

Dropped by phantoms when killed by a player or a tamed wolf.
Gifted by cats.

Obtained by trading with a wandering trader.
Can grow into larger stalactites or stalagmites.

Obtained by trading with a mason villager.
Crafted using renewable cobblestone and nether quartz.

Grown on farmland.
Rarely dropped by zombies when killed by a player or tamed wolf.
A cauldron in a snowy biome will fill up with powder snow when it is snowing.

Prismarine crystals and Prismarine shard dropped by guardians.
Prismarine crystals also obtained from breaking sea lanterns.
